PAWS - R Ladies Community Data Project

Ramaa Nathan

2/27/2019

petpoint.csv

Summary of Transformations: 1. DOB: Convert from character to Date Type using : lubridate::mdy(dob)

  1. intake_date, release_date, outcome_date: convert to POSIX using mdy_hm()

  2. Convert all other character types to factor types

  3. Create time intervals and and time period caterogies to track time from intake to outcome.

Summary of data: using skimr::skim(petpoint)

Questions: 1. NAME: Regional name: Data is a number string. Are these IDS?

  1. There are 12 entries with intake_age = -1 months and 312 entries with intake_age=0 months. What is the difference between them?

  2. ZipCode: there are 41 entries with invalid zipcodes (length < 5)

  3. There are 308 trello_ids where there is more than one duplicate of outcome_trello_id. On checking, we find 242 entries with 2 duplicates, 10 ids with three dupliates, 2 ids with 4 duplciates each, and 1 id with 5 duplicates
